data.title: If You and your Wallet are Tired of the Fancy Eating Places; Have a Regular Meal & a Slice of Pie
data.text: In Rochester, MN for the Mayo Clinic.  Had eaten at a handful of fancy restaurants last week (Oct. 17) with very good meals and now wanted a regular chain restaurant that is known in MN and other Midwestern states.  We were seated promptly with server asking for our drink order soon thereafter.  Meals were good and showed up in reasonable time. Just the right size to allow for dessert.  Pie selections were just right.  Many to choose from.

data.title: Stick to the pies
data.text: The menu looked promising, but the portions were not exactly what I expected. Plates had a fair amount of empty space. Fish & chips consisted of 2 small pieces but a good number of fries. Chicken breast was also on the small side, even for the 1 piece size. The only food that was hot was my squash soup. Food took a long time coming, and the place was not busy. Waitress did not ask how the food was and when we went to pay the bill, the cashier was preoccupied talking on her cell phone. The peanut butter pie, however, was tasty.

data.title: Manager is unprofessional
data.text: So me and the boyfriend decided to come here for lunch today when we walked in we didn't see any employees so we seated are selves because no "please wait to be seated sign was posted. The manager then said to our waitress I don't know what's going on back their but they seated themselves, he then went to the back kitchen where we could here him bashing us. If it wasn't for our waitress Dana who had a very strong personality and customer service skills we would have walked right out the door. Never should a Manager be the reason you want to leave, as we probably will never come to this baker square again. Just wanted to leave this review here, to let those know, how you may be treated by the manager. Food is great though.

data.title: Breakfast with the family
data.text: We met our son and his family here last Saturday after his oldest sons football game.  His team won, by the way.  We were seated at a big round table with plenty of room.  Denise was our waitress and is a real peach.  Fun to talk with and very knowledgeable about the menu.  We all had breakfast.  Two of us had the sausage benedict, which was wonderful.  One had regular eggs benedict and the others had omelets.  Everything was great and there was lots of it.  The only thing that wasn't good was that the wait staff kept cutting through the table area where we were seated.

data.title: Good food, generous portions
data.text: Ive read other reviews about this location of Bakers Square that complained of slow service.  Granted, I was there on a Tuesday evening at dinnertime with not many other guests, however the service was just fine.  It was the quality of food that impressed me.  I love a good pot roast and theirs was excellent.  I've had it at the Bakers Square near where I live - Gurnee, IL.  The portion was double what I've had previously and really tasty.  I also had the peach pie and it was awesome- I think it is hard to find a good peach pie.  I was very happy with my experience.

data.title: A long wait for good food.
data.text: We were seated immediately but the food wait time was quite a bit longer than expected. We got a few dirty utenciles which was replaced. The food was good. The waitress was very polite and attentive to our needs, especially to the kids.

data.title: Good food, wait time excessive
data.text: We arrived on a Thursday about 6PM.  Waited to be seated, although no line.  Waitress delivered menus promptly, but since this was a first time, we weren't ready to order immediately.  She allowed a long pause until her return visit.  We each ordered the roast beef over potatoes and a small side salad.  Didn't clock it, but more than half an hour elapsed before the food appeared.  The food was very good, very close to home cooking.  Wish the service was quicker.  Spoke later with a friend who also liked the food but deleted from their preferences list because of the very slow service.  Close to average speed would suffice;  our delay was excessive.

data.title: Extremely long wait for food
data.text: We ate here on a Wed. evening, not realizing it was "Free Pie Wednesday". We were seated almost immediately, but then waited over 40 minutes for our food.  Another couple, seated when we got there, was also waiting that long. The waitress was very cheerful and polite, and took our orders within about 10 minutes of getting seated, but it was obvious they needed additional help.  The food, when we finally did get it, was very tasty, and the free pie was a nice treat.

data.title: A return to an old haunt.
data.text: It's been many years since we ate here.  It hasn't changed.  The food is still good as well as  the pie.  I had 1/2 BLT with a salad and slice of pie.  The bacon was tasty and the b read warm.  My wife had her usual eggs benedict with extra sauce. To finish it off, we shared cocanut cream pie.  As good as ever.  Maddie was our server and was very attentive.

data.title: Very Good  FOOD!!
data.text: I have never have eaten at a Bakers Square before. I was so impressed with the food!! We came back 3 days in a row! The value of what paid for the meal was excellent!! We would recommend your restaurant to everyone!! Thank You

data.title: My Favorite Pie!
data.text: My favorite pie ever is the Caramel Supreme Silk Pie found only at Baker's Square.  We don't have this restaurant chain where I live so I'm always happy when I have a chance to visit one in another city.  I didn't eat a meal here the day I got my pie so I gave it one star less siince I really couldn't speak to their regular service or menu items.  I just know that I was thrilled that I could pick up a piece of my favorite to take out and enjoy at my leisure.  It was perfection!

data.title: Excellent Pies
data.text: Just enjoyed a wonderful piece of Banana Cream Pie. The bananas were just the right consistency.   Great service and very pleasant waitress.    If you want a sandwich and fries, they have that also., as well as other entrees.

data.title: Good menu and good for a chain
data.text: Bakers Square has an appealing menu for routine dining out: breakfast all day, pot pies, sandwiches, burgers, salads. Entrees are homey:pot roast, roasted turkey, mac & cheese, fish and chips.  Pies are the specialty, especially dessert pies.  Service was good and helpful.  Basically the food is acceptable  though nothing stood out as outstanding  The pies were fine but certainly not "the best pie in America" as they promote.  The pie pastry could be better; fruit fillings seemed very good.  This midwestern chain is certainly offering home cooking-style food at fair prices.  I think aspects of the Rochester, MN, store could have seemed cleaner, especially the bakery case displaying pies and the windows, which made one wonder if the whole store could be cleaner.

data.title: Slow and cold
data.text: Stopped on our way back home from a trip to Minneapolis. We all ordered their 4 items for 7.69. We waited a very long time ... At least 1/2 hour -40 minutes.  I ordered scrambled eggs, hash browns, sausage patty and a biscuit with gravy. Everything I ordered was cold. The scrambled eggs were so over cooked they were  crispy. I didn't send back since we waited so long and need to get back on the road.  I'm giving a 3 because the rest of the family did get warm food. We did buy a pie to bring home.

data.title: So slow!
data.text: We went this past Wednesday. Their menu was huge, with lots of different selections. The waitress was pleasant. We were also informed on Wednesdays we got a free slice of pie with our meals! We waited on our food for over an hour with only one drink refill. We went ahead and ordered our pie when our food finally came out thinking that would speed things up. Or food was good, but cold. We also had to eat our meal without drinks. The pie didn't arrive until 30 after we finished dinner, and the ticket 15 after that. We arrived before 5 and didn't get out until 7:30!!! Good, but not worth the wait.

data.title: Great Late Night Food
data.text: Great place to go with friends and have comfort food. Or with family. I grew up going to this place and it's always as good as I remember:)

data.title: Pleasantly surprised
data.text: I hadn't been to a Baker's Square in more than ten years, but my mom wanted to go and so we did. I was impressed with the menu and  food. My mom ordered Reuben Sandwich and it looked terrific. I went with Turkey/Dressing/Mashed Potatoes and it was the best outside of a Thanksgiving dinner. I'm going back for that (and perhaps other entrees.) Also, it was Wednesday and we got free pie. My french silk was tasty. My mom was disappointed in sour cream raisin. Didn't like the whipped topping.

data.title: Excellent service
data.text: We had excellent service at the restaurant.  Not only was our server prompt and correct with the order but a manager stopped by twice to be sure everything was OK.  A different waiter noticed our water glasses weren't full when she went by and offered to fill them too.

data.title: Not just Pie!
data.text: Known for outstanding pies, but also a very broad selection, with breakfast any time. Often busy Sundays late morning, but they get people seated pretty quickly.

data.title: Has gone downhill
data.text: Took 45 minutes to get our food.  Hamburger was way  underdone and French fries were cold.  Complained and god free pie
